value: Palearctic winter visitor, usually freshwater: North Africa, Nile Valley, Sahel zone and reaches equator in Kenya; carolinenesis is a vagrant to N Atlantic Is.

Shallow lakes, marshes, ponds, pools, and shallow streams with emergent vegetation; in winter, both fresh-water and brackish situations around marshes, shallow lakes, estuaries, and wet and flooded fields.

subcat_descr: Bill length (sex unknown) - Nares to tip

value: ground displays, but with occasional jumps/leaps into the air
